Inventory Management System – Backend

A simple backend application for managing products and inventory, built using Spring Boot and PostgreSQL.
Designed for college projects, learning REST APIs, and full-stack integration with React.

Tech Stack

    Backend
    Java 20
    Spring Boot
    Spring Data JPA
    Hibernate
    PostgreSQL
    Maven
    Tools

Postman (API testing)
pgAdmin / psql
IntelliJ IDEA

Project Structure
==================
com.inventory
 ├── controller
 ├── service
 │    └── impl
 ├── repository
 ├── entity
 ├── exception
 └── InventoryApplication.java

Database Schema
================
  Product Table
    Column	      Type
    id	          BIGSERIAL (PK)
    product_name	VARCHAR
    category	  VARCHAR
    quantity	  INT
    price	      DOUBLE

  Users Table
    Column	      Type
    id	          BIGSERIAL (PK)
    username	  VARCHAR
    password	  VARCHAR
    role	      VARCHAR (optional)

API Endpoints
===============
  Product APIs
    Method	 Endpoint	              Description
    POST	/api/products	          Add product
    GET	    /api/products	          Get all products
    PUT	    /api/products/{id}	      Update product
    DELETE	/api/products/{id}	      Delete product
    GET	    /api/products/low-stock	  Low stock products

  Auth API
    Method	Endpoint	              Description
    POST	/api/auth/login	          User login

  Sample JSON (Add Product)
{
  "productName": "Monitor",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 5,
  "price": 12000
}

Exception Handling
====================

Custom ResourceNotFoundException
Global exception handling using @RestControllerAdvice
Returns proper HTTP status codes (404, 400)


How to Run the Project
=======================

Clone the repository
Create PostgreSQL database
Update application.properties

Run:
mvn spring-boot:run

Server runs on:
http://localhost:9999

Testing
========

All APIs tested using Postman
CRUD operations verified
Database persistence verified using PostgreSQL

Future Enhancements
=====================
JWT authentication
Role-based access
Pagination & sorting
Frontend dashboard integration

